title: 911 call indicates Lamar Odom used cocaine, herbal sexual enhancement over three days at Nevada brothel
text: 911 call indicates Lamar Odom used cocaine, herbal sexual enhancement over three days at Nevada brothel Oct. 14, 2015 Updated 10:48 p.m. 1 of 5 Richard Hunter, media director for Dennis Hof, who owns the Love Ranch brothel in Crystal, Nev., walks in the room Wednesday were former NBA basketball player Lamar Odom was found unconscious the day before. CHRIS CARLSON, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 5 A sign advertises the Love Ranch brothel, in Crystal, Nev., where former NBA star Lamar Odom was found unconscious Tuesday. CHRIS CARLSON, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 5 Steps lead to the entrance to the suite at the Love Ranch brothel in Crystal, Nev., were former NBA basketball player Lamar Odom was found unconscious the day before. CHRIS CARLSON, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 5 Richard Hunter, media director for Dennis Hof, who owns the Love Ranch in Crystal, Nev., talks Wednesday about how he found former NBA basketball player Lamar Odom unconscious the day before. CHRIS CARLSON, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 5 In this 2009 file photo, Khloe Kardashian and Lakers player Lamar Odom pose at a movie premier in Los Angeles. Odom remained hospitalized Wednesday and Kardashian, his estranged wife, was by his side after he was found unresponsive in a Nevada brothel Tuesday. CHRIS PIZZELLO, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS
